Package ajeffrey.teaching.util.list

Contains an example container data structure.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FlyweightImmutableList
    This is an implementation of immutable lists, using the `Flyweight' pattern from the `Gang of Four' book (this technique is also called `hash consing' in the LISP world).
    ImmutableList
    An immutable ordered collection of elements.
    Iterator
    An iterator over a collection.
    MutableList
    An ordered collection of elements.
    MutableListFactory
    A factory for building list objects.

Package ajeffrey.teaching.util.list Description

Contains an example container data structure. This data structure is intended as an example of the techniques for developing thread-safe containers.
